            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">To anticipate their desires, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">to let their strong men to submit, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">to investigate their worries </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">to be quiet and therefore to attend (to circumstances), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">to wait for the (right) time to set out (for action) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">because of this, while toiling on their duty and issuing policies, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en">governors should not forget about how to make affairs orderly </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">person, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">can be called minister of the state. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">The duke said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">may I ask about the affairs of the people? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">[...] Confucius </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">Peasants should be encouraged to plow, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">to fill the official granaries </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">The hundred craftsmen should be encouraged (to take care of) their affairs, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">to fill the government deposits </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">The common people should be encouraged (to take care of) the cultivation of their four limbs, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0049_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">to make provisions for the army [...] </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
